    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-09-07T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-09-07T07:00:00-05:00" n="634"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d634">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.852/33: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Standley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-09-07T15:00:00+03:00"
                            >September 7, 1943—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 8—10:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1283. To Stettinius from Faymonville.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Has final decision been taken on five ships to be transferred to Soviet
                        registry during September? Commissar believes that it is great importance to
                        effect transfer without delay.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Because of shipping delays which Krutikov says will result in
                        accumulations of freight ports during October, Commissar asks that you
                        approve project for transfer of five additional ships to Soviet flag during
                            October.<note n="27" xml:id="d634fn27">
                            <p>In telegram No. 818, September 9, 1943, Lend-Lease Administrator
                                Stettinius replied as follows: <list>
                                    <item>“1. It has been found impossible to grant the request in
                                        your 1283 although it has received serious sympathetic
                                        consideration.</item>
                                    <item>“2. The transfer is arranged of a tanker having capacity
                                        of 55,000 barrels. Although no decision yet made the
                                        possibility of a further transfer of a 75,000 barrel tanker
                                        is under consideration and study.” (861.852/33)</item>
                                </list>
                            </p>
                        </note> [Faymonville.]</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Standley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
